</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ujustallyssia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Just Allyssia</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ichuu.com/anicat.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Uberlicious Admin</span><br> <font color=#778899>(2/20/02 11:13:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1170.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.ichuu.com/amazonally.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Cost of EZBoard</span><hr size=1> Average Daily Statistics<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.ichuu.com/Ally/Stats.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ugamiene.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gamiene</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amiable Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(2/21/02 3:43:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1170.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Cost of EZBoard</span><hr size=1> Tugurok's inferences aside, counting on people to remember to support this place is likely not the best method to ensure it gets paid for... those who donated this time may or may not do so again... and those who did not may not ever. It is more feasible and less stressful to mitigate traffic as much as possible, hopefully without impacting community services too much. <br>
<br>
One way would be to eliminate titles completely. Another would be to eliminate or regularly purge (read: remove aged) posts. Another would be to eliminate as much in the way of graphical items being posted here as possible. If someone really needs a complete archive of everything that ever happened here, they should consider either buying a CDRW or a larger chunk of space on their personal drive (i.e. Usenet archives, etc.).<br>
<br>
I'm sure traffic analysis would reveal which forums we could live without.... not that there isn't a certain segment who will howl that you're ripping their livers out regardless the lack of traffic. <br>
<br>
Perhaps a good way to go about it would be to announce a monitoring period with the specific goal of eliminating forums where traffic is &lt; 10% of over-all board traffic. Maintain regular analysis of page hits during that time, and cull forums accordingly. <br>
<br>
Indeed, there is no reason why one couldn't combine playground and ooc, since the post types in each are often very similar. By the same token, the majority of posts in 'general' could be made under 'guilds' or 'news' or 'rants'. So there's another possible reduction to be made.<br>
<br>
The 'ask the staff' forum could be eliminated in favor of an email link, and the 'news' forum could be elminated for the innoruuk.com splash page (index.html)... especially since people can add news these days.<br>
<br>
My $0.02 worth.<br>
 <p><HR><BR>
