 section.<br>
<br>
I do think more aggressive archiving of posts -- especially in the trades section -- could reduce costs.  Or someone could help write an auction system to run on inny.com that would facilitate searches -- dramatically reducing activity by not having to view a bunch of posts looking for what you're trying to buy.<br>
<br>
However, none of these steps will *significantly* make much difference.  I think if roughly 30 days before Gold Status is going to expire, Ally posts a &quot;time to donate again&quot; thread, we'll get enough people to pitch in a few dollars each.  That's just my opinion.<br>
<br>
Gam's right -- it may not be the same people.  And the people who didn't kick in this time may not kick in next time.  But the people who use these boards are *for the most part* good, responsible people who value what the boards offer.  I have faith in the overall goodness of the people here.<br>
<br>
But then, I'm a programmer.  We're born optimists.  Ever seen the timelines we publish for when software will be completed?<br>
